# .fridayrules
# Purpose: Fast on-ramp for contributors.
# Sections: ARCH, TEST, LINT. (<50 lines total)

ARCH
- Template generates one of six project flavours: full | api | cli | data_science | automation | minimal.
- Source layout: either src/<<slug>> or flat, governed by `use_src_layout`.
- Core tooling: pyproject.toml (PEP 621), uv (lock + run), justfile (task runner).

TEST
- Framework: pytest (+pytest-cov).
- All tests live in tests/**.
- Run quick suite:            `just test`
- Run with HTML coverage:      `just test-cov`
- Coverage gate (%): defined by `tool.pytest.ini_options.cov-fail-under` in pyproject.toml.

LINT
- Ruff handles style, imports, bugbear, etc.
- Auto-fix + format whole tree: `just lint` & `just format`.
- CI parity check (no writes):  `just check`.
- Optional extras wired via pre-commit: mypy (typing) & deptry (deps).

# end
